claim.claim-text:
1. A method of operating a wireless network, comprising:
creating a resource block map by associating subscriber station identifications, corresponding to respective subscriber stations, with one or more resource blocks;
scheduling indicators in the resource block map for resource blocks assigned more than one respective subscriber station, each of the indicators being associated with one of the one or more resource blocks and indicating a total number of respective subscriber stations assigned to an associated one of the one or more resource blocks;
transmitting the respective subscriber station identifications in one or more control channel symbols; and
transmitting the resource block map in a shared resource block mapping channel.

10. A serving apparatus, comprising:
a wireless interface configured to communicate with a population of subscriber station devices;
a processor; and
a computer readable apparatus having a storage medium with at least one computer program stored thereon, the at least one computer program configured to, when executed on the processor:
create a resource block map configured to assign subscriber station identifications that correspond to respective subscriber stations to one or more resource blocks;
schedule indicators in the resource block map for resource blocks assigned more than one respective subscriber station, each of the indicators being associated with one of the one or more resource blocks and indicating a total number of respective subscriber stations assigned to an associated one of the one or more resource blocks;
transmit the respective subscriber station identifications in one or more control channel symbols; and
transmit the resource block map in a shared resource block mapping channel.

11. A method of operating a wireless network, comprising:
creating a resource block map by at least associating subscriber station identifications, corresponding to respective subscriber stations, with one or more resource blocks;
scheduling indicators in the resource block map for resource blocks assigned more than one respective subscriber station, each of the indicators being associated with one of the one or more resource blocks and relating to a total number of respective subscriber stations assigned to an associated one of the one or more resource blocks;
transmitting the respective subscriber station identifications in one or more control channel symbols; and
transmitting the resource block map via a shared resource block mapping channel.

12. A serving apparatus, comprising:
a wireless interface configured to communicate with a population of subscriber station devices;
a processor; and
a computer readable apparatus in data communication with the processor and having a storage medium with at least one computer program stored thereon, the at least one computer program configured to, when executed on the processor:
create a resource block map configured to assign subscriber station identifications that correspond to respective subscriber stations to one or more resource blocks;
schedule indicators in the resource block map for resource blocks assigned more than one respective subscriber station, each of the indicators being associated with one of the one or more resource blocks and indicating a total number of respective subscriber stations assigned to an associated one of the one or more resource blocks;
transmit the respective subscriber station identifications in one or more control channel symbols; and
transmit the resource block map using a shared resource block mapping channel.
